request.description:
**Description**:

- Fetches all notifications for the patient identified by the ABHA address.

- Notifications can include updates on health records, care contexts, or system alerts relevant to the patient.


**Response:**

``` json
[
{
        "_id": "692814c285ba3f96714ffdf5",
        "type": "INFO",
        "module": "NEW_CARE_CONTEXT",
        "message": "New HealthDocumentRecord type health record created.",
        "seen": false,
        "abhaAddress": "suhaas_2025@sbx",
        "metadata": {
            "event": {
                "id": "6a1b68a0-46a3-48fe-9598-43310a696b13",
                "published": "2025-11-27 09:07:14.095",
                "category": "LINK",
                "content": {
                    "patient": {
                        "id": "suhaas_2025@sbx"
                    },
                    "hip": {
                        "id": "IN0510000753"
                    },
                    "contexts": [
                        {
                            "careContexts": [
                                {
                                    "patientReference": "ARID1",
                                    "careContextReference": "692814c285ba3f96714ffdde-HealthDocumentRecord"
                                }
                            ],
                            "hiType": "HealthDocumentRecord"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            }
        },
        "createdAt": "2025-11-27T09:07:14.811Z",
        "updatedAt": "2025-11-27T09:07:14.811Z",
        "__v": 0
    }
]

 ```

**Notes:**

- Requires a valid JWT token for authentication.

- The ABHA address in the path and headers should match the logged-in patient.

- Response includes both read and unread notifications.

