request.description:
**Description**

- Marks a specific notification as “seen” for the patient, updating its read status in the system.


**Path Parameter:**

- `notificationId` – The unique ID of the notification to mark as seen.


**Respose:**

``` json
{
    "_id": "69281417e2bda294479b9cec",
    "type": "INFO",
    "module": "NEW_CARE_CONTEXT",
    "message": "New HealthDocumentRecord type health record created.",
    "seen": true,
    "abhaAddress": "suhaas_2025@sbx",
    "metadata": {
        "event": {
            "id": "31ba0fb3-e5fa-4e91-828b-8bc0cb0f41e8",
            "published": "2025-11-27 09:04:23.135",
            "category": "LINK",
            "content": {
                "patient": {
                    "id": "suhaas_2025@sbx"
                },
                "hip": {
                    "id": "IN0510000753"
                },
                "contexts": [
                    {
                        "careContexts": [
                            {
                                "patientReference": "ARID1",
                                "careContextReference": "69281417e2bda294479b9cd9-HealthDocumentRecord"
                            }
                        ],
                        "hiType": "HealthDocumentRecord"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    },
    "createdAt": "2025-11-27T09:04:23.992Z",
    "updatedAt": "2025-12-04T06:31:54.090Z",
    "__v": 0
}

 ```

**Notes**:

- Requires a valid JWT token and matching ABHA address.

- After this call, the notification’s `read`/`seen` status will be updated in subsequent fetches.

