                                "description": "<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-9192460e-7fff-a1ce-487d-d51536b33e62\"></strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; text-align: left; background-color: #ffffff; float: none;\">Basic vital organ screen comprises a group of tests to evaluate the overall health of an individual. It is used to detect disorders such as diabetes, thyroid disorders, kidney disease and liver disease through some markers. The package also includes a complete evaluation of blood parameters which can give clue for a number of other diseases. The package can be ordered as a part of routine check up to monitor general health. The package is also useful for the patients already suffering from some diseases such as diabetes, kidney diseases, liver disease, thyroid diseases, and anemia to check the progress of treatment.</span></p>",
